<sec>
<st>
Brief History</st>

<p>

ValCom was founded in 1983 as a hardware-driven company with a Fortune 500 account focus.  In the early nineties, ValCom realigned the business to focus in IT services and later developed its own software to manage those services.  In 2000, ValCom brought the tool to the web.  ValCom spread into the Strategic Staffing Services sector the following year.  In 2005, ValCom licensed its web-based tool, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../959/18743959.xml">
WebSPOC</link> <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%227%22])">7</ref> , and offered it with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../333/2262333.xml">
SaaS</link><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%228%22])">8</ref>, hosted, or licensing options.  ValCom's Security division earned <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../824/1108824.xml">
PCI</link> certification<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%225%22])">5</ref>, in 2008.</p>

